== NEMETIC PHI :: S12B Energy Leak Violation Frame ==

Φ(Energy Leak Violation Frame) = σ(spiritual|wellness) ∘ ρ(depletion|drain) ∘ λ(blame|externalization) ∘ β(withdrawal|protection) ∘ δγ(embodied|fatigue) ∘ μ(metaphor|structure) + ε | :defensive_conservation

--- Operator Breakdown ---

σ (Air / Signal):
  Spiritual and wellness discourse provides the signaling medium. Language of "energy,"
  "vibration," "draining," and "leaking" circulates through wellness communities,
  social media, and therapeutic spaces. The signal layer borrows from both new-age
  spirituality and pop-psychology to frame emotional experience as energetic transaction.

ρ (Water / Resonance):
  Felt depletion is the experiential core. The emotional reality of exhaustion, fatigue,
  and relational drain provides the water that gives the metaphor its felt truth. People
  genuinely feel depleted — the question is whether the "leak" framing accurately
  describes the mechanism or merely validates a particular interpretation.

λ (Fire / Catalyst):
  Blame externalization ignites when the leak frame shifts from internal experience to
  interpersonal accusation. The catalytic moment: "I feel drained" becomes "they are
  draining me." Fire transforms a state description into a violation narrative, casting
  others as energy thieves rather than examining the full relational dynamic.

β (Wood / Growth):
  Withdrawal and self-protection grow as the sanctioned response. Once energy leak is
  established as violation, the organic next step is retreat, boundary-hardening, and
  relational pruning. The wood element expands the territory of what counts as a
  threatening interaction.

δγ (Earth / Ground):
  Embodied fatigue provides physical grounding. Tiredness, muscle tension, headaches,
  and lethargy are recruited as evidence that energy has literally been taken. The
  somatic dimension gives the metaphor a material anchor that makes it feel more real
  than "mere" metaphor.

μ (Metal / Structure):
  The energy-as-finite-resource metaphor provides structural constraint. Once energy is
  conceptualized as a depletable quantity, conservation logic follows inevitably.
  Spending becomes loss, interaction becomes transaction, and protection becomes
  hoarding. The metallic frame is rigid but limited.

--- Z-State ---
:defensive_conservation — the system settles into a posture of protecting remaining
energy reserves from perceived external threats. Stability is achieved through
withdrawal rather than engagement.

--- Tendency ---
ρ → 0.83 — felt emotional depletion dominates; the power of this meme rests on the
genuine experience of being drained, which the framing then channels into specific
interpretive and behavioral pathways.

# CE-STATE: multiscale
# EI-NOTE: Causal power distributed across multiple description levels
